La Puerta first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]]<ref name=2000CensusTX/> and was reduced in size prior to the [[2010 U.S. census]] after 2 new CDPS ([[B and E, Texas|B and E]], [[Garza-Salinas II, Texas|Garza-Salinas II]]) were carved out of its territory.<ref name=2010CensusTX/>

